7. Urges Israel to withdraw from northern Ghajar without delay in coordination with UNIFIL;

8. Reaffirms the need for an area free of armed personnel, assets, and weapons between the Blue Line and the Litani River;

9. Welcomes UNIFIL's efforts to implement the zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;

10. Requests the Secretary-General to report on the implementation of resolution 1701 (2006) every four months;

11. Stresses the importance of a comprehensive, just, and lasting peace in the Middle East based on relevant resolutions;

12. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
